goals.question: What is the distribution of population by education level?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('population.json')

# Plot
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x="age_group", y="population", data=data, ax=ax, color='b')
ax.set_xlabel('Age Group')
ax.set_ylabel('Population')
plt.title('What is the distribution of population by age group?', wrap=True)

# Return plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('population.json')

# Convert date field to date type
data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')

# Create line chart
sns.lineplot(x='year', y='population', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over the years?', wrap=True)

# Set x-axis label rotation
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('population.json')

# Pie chart of population by gender
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
sns.set_palette("pastel")
sns.set(font_scale=1.2)
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
ax = sns.countplot(x="gender", data=data, palette="pastel")
ax.set_title("What is the distribution of population by gender?")
ax.set_xlabel("Gender")
ax.set_ylabel("Count")
ax.legend(title="Gender", labels=["Female", "Male"])
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns

# Load data

# Plot stacked bar chart of population by education level
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
sns.set_palette("husl")
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(10,6)})
sns.barplot(x="education_level", y="population", hue="gender", data=data, estimator=sum)
plt.title("What is the distribution of population by education level?", wrap=True)

# Show plot
plt.show()
